  "response_text": "A bright, graphic title card appears against a teal-green background: a rounded red-orange rectangle with a thick yellow border. In loose white handwritten lettering, it asks, “Need a better all purpose cleaner?” The card settles fully into view, like a bold sign or placard.\n\nThe scene changes to a white bathroom sink from a low, close angle. A young child, likely a girl with dark hair and an orange top, leans over the basin and reaches in with a red-orange sponge. Her arm stretches across the sink as she wipes around the drain and under the shiny metal faucet. The sink surface is visibly marked with scattered dark grime and smudges. The sponge moves across the basin, then is lifted away, leaving the dirty white surface still visible in places.\n\nA small shaggy dog with white and tan fur stands on a light-colored floor near a bright red food bowl. The bowl is full, and kibble is scattered around it in a messy ring. The dog lowers its head and eats from the floor and bowl, while crumbs and pellets remain spread across the floor around its paws.\n\nThe setting shifts to a dirty kitchen stovetop. A glass or metal pan with browned, crusted food sits on the burner area. Around it, the stovetop is spattered with greasy liquid, dark burnt bits, and food residue. The view moves across stove knobs and a long metal strip between burners, all dotted with grime and oily spots, emphasizing the sticky, cooked-on mess.\n\nA large white plastic bottle of Comet Cleaner with Bleach is then shown prominently. It has a built-in handle on the right side and a green label with a red-and-yellow Comet logo, a yellow star, and the words “Comet Cleaner with Bleach.” A small cleaning pail graphic appears near the lower part of the label. The bottle is clean and brightly lit, standing out against a white background.\n\nA comparison demonstration follows on a white stovetop divided by a vertical line down the middle, with black coil burners on both sides. At the top, large text reads “Tough Greasy Dirt,” with smaller comparison text beneath it that is present but not fully legible. At the lower left, the left side is labeled “LEADING BLEACH CLEANER,” and at the lower right, the Comet logo marks the right side. Two hands use yellow cloths to wipe both sides at the same time, rubbing upward and downward around the burners. The cloth on the Comet side moves over the right half while the other cloth works the left half, visually comparing how the greasy dirt comes off. By the end of the wiping, the surfaces look much cleaner, with the right Comet side presented alongside the Comet logo.\n\nThe commercial returns to a close view of the Comet bottle label, filling most of the image. The green label, yellow star, red logo panel, and white “Comet” lettering are large and clear, with the handle visible along the right edge of the bottle.\n\nFinally, the bottle appears on the left side of another red-orange rounded sign with the same thick yellow border and teal-green background. A small oval near the bottle’s shoulder reads “NEW!” On the right, white handwritten text says, “When others can’t cut it, Comet can.” The Comet Cleaner with Bleach bottle remains displayed beside the slogan as the ad ends.",
